log_cols = ["duration", "src_bytes", "dst_bytes", "hot", "num_failed_logins", "num_compromised", "num_root", "num_file_creations", 
            "num_shells", "num_access_files"]

dataframe = X_train

for log_col in log_cols:
    if log_col in dataframe.columns:
        print("Processing column: %s" %(log_col))
        dataframe[log_col] = dataframe[log_col].map(lambda x: max(np.log(x), 0))
    else:
        pass

In [21]:
# Normalizing the values
dataframe = X_train_log_transformed
norm_type = "mean-std"

for numeric_col in numeric_cols:
    if numeric_col in dataframe.columns:
        print("Processing column: %s" %(numeric_col))
        values = dataframe[numeric_col]
        if norm_type == "min-max":
            dataframe[numeric_col] = (values - np.min(values))/(np.max(values) - np.min(values))
            dataframe[numeric_col] = dataframe[numeric_col].astype("float")
        elif norm_type == "mean-std":
            dataframe[numeric_col] = (values - np.min(values))/np.std(values)
            dataframe[numeric_col] = dataframe[numeric_col].astype("float")
    else:
        pass
    
X_train_normalized = dataframe

def show_PCA_impt_info(X_train, all_feature_labels, display_amt):
    n_components = len(all_feature_labels)
    pca = PCA(n_components).fit(X_train)

    # generate PC labels:
    PCs=[]
    for l in range(1,n_components+1):
        PCs.append("PC"+str(l))

    # Get Eigenvectors & Eigenvalues
    eigvec = pca.components_.transpose()
    eigval = pca.explained_variance_
    
    eigval = -np.sort(-eigval) #descending
    var_expln= pca.explained_variance_ratio_ * 100
    npc = display_amt # display-1
    print("Eigenvalues   :", eigval[0:npc])
    print("%Explained_Var:", var_expln[0:npc])
    print("%Cumulative   :", np.cumsum(var_expln[0:npc]))
    print('\n')
    
    num_vars= len(all_processed_features)
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))
    sing_vals = np.arange(num_vars) + 1

    plt.plot(sing_vals, eigval, 'ro-', linewidth=2)
    plt.title('Scree Plot')
    plt.xlabel('Principal Component')
    plt.ylabel('Eigenvalue')
    plt.grid(); plt.show()

Training the Model(s)¶

In [80]:
def train_KNN(X_train, Y_train, grid_search=False):
    
    cv_val = 3
    vb_lvl = 10
    
    params = {'n_neighbors':[3,5],
              'weights':['uniform','distance'],
              'algorithm': ['auto'],
              'p':[1,2]}
    
    if grid_search:
        search_clf = GridSearchCV(KNeighborsClassifier(), params, cv=cv_val, verbose=vb_lvl)
        
        #Learning
        search_clf.fit(X_train, Y_train)

        #The best hyper parameters set
        print("Best Hyper Parameters:", search_clf.best_params_)
        print('Best Score: ', search_clf.best_score_)
        
        best_n_neighbors = search_clf.best_params_["n_neighbors"]
        best_weights = search_clf.best_params_["weights"]
        best_algorithm = search_clf.best_params_["algorithm"]
        best_p = search_clf.best_params_["p"]
        
        clf = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=best_n_neighbors, 
                                     weights=best_weights,
                                     algorithm=best_algorithm, 
                                     p=best_p,
                                     n_jobs=-1)
        trained_clf = clf.fit(X_train, Y_train)
    else:
        clf = KNeighborsClassifier(algorithm='auto', weights='distance', n_neighbors=3, n_jobs=-1)
        trained_clf = clf.fit(X_train, Y_train)
    
    print("Training Accuracy is %s" %(trained_clf.score(X_train, Y_train)))
    
    return trained_clf

def train_SVC(X_train, Y_train, grid_search=False):
    
    cv_val = 3
    vb_lvl = 10
    
    params = {'C':[0.5,1,1.5],
              'kernel':['linear', 'rbf'],
              'shrinking': [True, False],
              'random_state':[0]}
    
    if grid_search:
        search_clf = GridSearchCV(SVC(probability=True), params, cv=cv_val, verbose=vb_lvl)
        
        #Learning
        search_clf.fit(X_train, Y_train)

        #The best hyper parameters set
        print("Best Hyper Parameters:", search_clf.best_params_)
        print('Best Score: ', search_clf.best_score_)
        
        best_C = search_clf.best_params_["C"]
        best_kernel = search_clf.best_params_["kernel"]
        best_shrinking = search_clf.best_params_["shrinking"]
        best_random_state = search_clf.best_params_["random_state"]
        
        clf = SVC(C=best_C,
                  kernel=best_kernel,
                  shrinking=best_shrinking,
                  random_state=best_random_state,
                  probability=True)
        trained_clf = clf.fit(X_train, Y_train)
    else:
        clf = SVC(C=1.5, degree=1, kernel='rbf', shrinking=True, probability=True, random_state=0)
        trained_clf = clf.fit(X_train, Y_train)
    
    print("Training Accuracy is %s" %(trained_clf.score(X_train, Y_train)))
    
    return trained_clf

def train_DTC(X_train, Y_train, grid_search=False):
    
    cv_val = 3
    vb_lvl = 10
    
    params = {'criterion':['gini','entropy'],
              'splitter':['best','random'],
              'max_features': ['auto', 'log2'],
              'max_depth':[3,5,7],
              'min_samples_leaf':[2,7],
              'min_samples_split':[2,7],
              'random_state':[0]}
    
    if grid_search:
        search_clf = GridSearchCV(DecisionTreeClassifier(), params, cv=cv_val, verbose=vb_lvl)
        
        #Learning
        search_clf.fit(X_train, Y_train)

        best_max_depth = search_clf.best_params_["max_depth"]
        best_min_samples_leaf = search_clf.best_params_["min_samples_leaf"]
        best_min_samples_split = search_clf.best_params_["min_samples_split"]
        best_random_state = search_clf.best_params_["random_state"]
        
        clf = DecisionTreeClassifier(criterion=best_criterion, 
                                     splitter=best_splitter,
                                     max_features=best_max_features, 
                                     max_depth=best_max_depth, 
                                     min_samples_leaf=best_min_samples_leaf,

                                     random_state=best_random_state)

    else:
        clf = DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=5, max_features="log2", random_state=0)
        trained_clf = clf.fit(X_train, Y_train)

def train_XGB(X_train, Y_train, grid_search=False):
    
    cv_val = 3
    vb_lvl = 10
    
    params = {'booster':['gbtree', 'gblinear', 'dart'],
              'n_estimators':[10,30,50],
              'max_depth':[3,5,7],
              'reg_lambda':[0.0,1.0,1.5,2.0],
              'random_state':[0],
              'n_jobs':[-1]}
    
    if grid_search:
        search_clf = GridSearchCV(xgboost.XGBClassifier(), params, cv=cv_val, verbose=vb_lvl)
        
        #Learning
        search_clf.fit(X_train, Y_train)

        #The best hyper parameters set
        print("Best Hyper Parameters:", search_clf.best_params_)
        print('Best Score: ', search_clf.best_score_)
        
        best_booster = search_clf.best_params_["booster"]
        best_n_estimators = search_clf.best_params_["n_estimators"]
        best_max_depth = search_clf.best_params_["max_depth"]
        best_reg_lamba = search_clf.best_params_["reg_lambda"]
        best_random_state = search_clf.best_params_["random_state"]
        best_n_jobs = search_clf.best_params_["n_jobs"]
        
        clf = xgboost.XGBClassifier(booster=best_booster,
                                     n_estimators=best_n_estimators, 
                                     max_depth=best_max_depth, 
                                     reg_lamba=best_reg_lamba,
                                     random_state=best_random_state,
                                     n_jobs=best_n_jobs)
        trained_clf = clf.fit(X_train, Y_train)
    else:
        clf = xgboost.XGBClassifier(max_depth=5, reg_lambda=2, random_state=0, n_jobs=-1)
        trained_clf = clf.fit(X_train, Y_train)
    
    print("Training Accuracy is %s" %(trained_clf.score(X_train, Y_train)))
    
    return trained_clf

# Normalizing the values
dataframe = X_test_log_transformed

print("Using the norm_type set above: %s \n" %(norm_type))

for numeric_col in numeric_cols:
    if numeric_col in dataframe.columns:
        print("Processing column: %s" %(numeric_col))
        values = dataframe[numeric_col]
        if norm_type == "min-max":
            dataframe[numeric_col] = (values - np.min(values))/(np.max(values) - np.min(values))
            dataframe[numeric_col] = dataframe[numeric_col].astype("float")
        elif norm_type == "mean-std":
            dataframe[numeric_col] = (values - np.min(values))/np.std(values)
            dataframe[numeric_col] = dataframe[numeric_col].astype("float")
    else:
        pass
    
X_test_normalized = dataframe

def get_ROC_plot_metrics(clf, label_val, X_test, Y_test):
    class_list = list(clf.classes_)
    index = class_list.index(label_val)
    predict_proba = clf.predict_proba(X_test)[::, index]
    fpr, tpr, threshold = roc_curve(Y_test, predict_proba, pos_label=label_val)
    auc = roc_auc_score(Y_test, predict_proba)
    
    return fpr, tpr, threshold, auc
In [159]:
def plot_ROCs(knn_clf, svc_clf, dtc_clf, rfc_clf, xgb_clf, vot_clf, iso_clf, label_val, X_test, Y_test):
    plt.figure(figsize=(20,10))
    if knn_clf:
        knn_fpr, knn_tpr, knn_threshold, knn_auc = get_ROC_plot_metrics(knn_clf, label_val, X_test, Y_test)
        plt.plot(knn_fpr, knn_tpr, label = "K Nearest Neighbours Classifier " + str(knn_auc))  
    if svc_clf:
        svc_fpr, svc_tpr, svc_threshold, svc_auc = get_ROC_plot_metrics(svc_clf, label_val, X_test, Y_test)
        plt.plot(svc_fpr, svc_tpr, label = "Support Vector Classifier " + str(svc_auc))
    if dtc_clf:
        dtc_fpr, dtc_tpr, dtc_threshold, dtc_auc = get_ROC_plot_metrics(dtc_clf, label_val, X_test, Y_test)
        plt.plot(dtc_fpr, dtc_tpr, label = "Decision Tree Classifier " + str(dtc_auc))
    if rfc_clf:
        rfc_fpr, rfc_tpr, rfc_threshold, rfc_auc = get_ROC_plot_metrics(rfc_clf, label_val, X_test, Y_test)
        plt.plot(rfc_fpr, rfc_tpr, label = "Random Forest Classifier " + str(rfc_auc))
    if xgb_clf:
        xgb_fpr, xgb_tpr, xgb_threshold, xgb_auc = get_ROC_plot_metrics(xgb_clf, label_val, X_test, Y_test)
        plt.plot(xgb_fpr, xgb_tpr, label = "XGBoost Classifier " + str(xgb_auc))
    if vot_clf:
        vot_fpr, vot_tpr, vot_threshold, vot_auc = get_ROC_plot_metrics(vot_clf, label_val, X_test, Y_test)
        plt.plot(vot_fpr, vot_tpr, label = "Voting Classifier " + str(vot_auc))
    if iso_clf:
        isofor_score_samples = iso_clf.score_samples(X_test)
        isofor_predict_proba = [-1*x for x in list(isofor_score_samples)] # Convert it from [-1, 0] to [0, 1]
        iso_fpr, iso_tpr, iso_threshold = roc_curve(Y_test, isofor_predict_proba, pos_label=label_val)
        iso_auc = roc_auc_score(Y_test, isofor_predict_proba)
        plt.plot(iso_fpr, iso_tpr, label = "Isolation Forest Classifier " + str(iso_auc))
    
    plt.xlabel('FPR', fontsize=10)
    plt.ylabel('TPR', fontsize=10)
    plt.title("ROC Curve")
    plt.plot([0,1],[0,1], "k--")
    plt.legend(loc=4)
    plt.show()
In [160]:
def output_metrics(tmp_clf, X_test, Y_test, label, threshold=0.5):
    print("For", label, "\n")
    
    if threshold == 0.5:
        predict = tmp_clf.predict(X_test)
    else:
        # Index is required as it's swapped sometimes, for RFC/ XGB/ others
        class_list = tmp_clf.classes_
        print(class_list)
        index = list(class_list).index(label)
        predict_prob = tmp_clf.predict_proba(X_test)[::, index]
        predict = []
        for prob in predict_prob:
            if prob >= threshold:
                predict.append(label)
            else:
                predict.append("normal")
    
    acc_sc = accuracy_score(Y_test, predict)
    print("Accuracy is")
    print(acc_sc)
    
    print("\nConfusion Matrix")
    cm = confusion_matrix(Y_test, predict, labels = ["normal", label])
    for row in cm:
        print(row)
    
    print("\n Classification Report")
    print(classification_report(Y_test, predict))
In [161]:
def prettify_decimals(int_val, round_digits=4):
    """
    Note, returns a string value
    """
    pretty_str = str(round(int_val, round_digits)).ljust(round_digits + 2, '0')
    return pretty_str
In [162]:
def output_metrics2(tmp_clf, X_test, Y_test, label_val, threshold_range):
    print("For", label_val, "\n")
    
    round_digits = 3
    
    # Index is required as it's swapped sometimes, for RFC/ XGB/ others
    class_list = tmp_clf.classes_
    index = list(class_list).index(label_val)
    predict_prob = tmp_clf.predict_proba(X_test)[::, index]
    
    for threshold in threshold_range:
        threshold = round(threshold,round_digits)
        predict = []
        for prob in predict_prob:
            if prob >= threshold:
                predict.append(label_val)
            else:
                predict.append("normal")
                
        acc_sc = prettify_decimals(accuracy_score(Y_test, predict), round_digits)
        label_precision_src = prettify_decimals(precision_score(Y_test, predict, pos_label=label_val), round_digits)
        norm_precision_src = prettify_decimals(precision_score(Y_test, predict, pos_label="normal"), round_digits)
        label_recall_src = prettify_decimals(recall_score(Y_test, predict, pos_label=label_val), round_digits)
        norm_recall_src = prettify_decimals(recall_score(Y_test, predict, pos_label="normal"), round_digits)
        label_f1_scr = prettify_decimals(f1_score(Y_test, predict, pos_label=label_val), round_digits)
        norm_f1_scr = prettify_decimals(f1_score(Y_test, predict, pos_label="normal"), round_digits)

        print("(Thr): %s, (Acc): %s, (Prec) Label: %s Norm: %s, (Rec) Label: %s Norm: %s, (F1) Label: %s Norm: %s" 
              %(prettify_decimals(threshold, 2), acc_sc, label_precision_src, norm_precision_src, label_recall_src, norm_recall_src, label_f1_scr, norm_f1_scr))

def output_metrics_isofor2(tmp_clf, X_test, Y_test, label_val, threshold_range):
    print("For", label_val, "\n")
    
    round_digits = 3
    
    predict_prob = -1*tmp_clf.score_samples(X_test[all_processed_features]) # Convert it from [-1, 0] to [0, 1]
    
    for threshold in threshold_range:
        threshold = round(threshold,round_digits)
        predict = []
        for prob in predict_prob:
            if prob >= threshold:
                predict.append(label_val)
            else:
                predict.append("normal")
                
        acc_sc = prettify_decimals(accuracy_score(Y_test, predict), round_digits)
        label_precision_src = prettify_decimals(precision_score(Y_test, predict, pos_label=label_val), round_digits)
        norm_precision_src = prettify_decimals(precision_score(Y_test, predict, pos_label="normal"), round_digits)
        label_recall_src = prettify_decimals(recall_score(Y_test, predict, pos_label=label_val), round_digits)
        norm_recall_src = prettify_decimals(recall_score(Y_test, predict, pos_label="normal"), round_digits)
        label_f1_scr = prettify_decimals(f1_score(Y_test, predict, pos_label=label_val), round_digits)
        norm_f1_scr = prettify_decimals(f1_score(Y_test, predict, pos_label="normal"), round_digits)

        print("(Thr): %s, (Acc): %s, (Prec) Label: %s Norm: %s, (Rec) Label: %s Norm: %s, (F1) Label: %s Norm: %s" 
              %(prettify_decimals(threshold, 2), acc_sc, label_precision_src, norm_precision_src, label_recall_src, norm_recall_src, label_f1_scr, norm_f1_scr))

    print("\nConfusion Matrix")
    cm = confusion_matrix(Y_test, predict, labels = ["normal", label])
    for row in cm:
        print(row)
    
    print("\n Classification Report")
    print(classification_report(Y_test, predict))
